history.content: Provided you have a relatively strong linear algebra background (since 127 strongly assumes that), the first plan seems reasonable. Otherwise, you could pair up 140 with Math 110 and take 127 the following semester.

Hello. I'm a Data Science sophomore planning on graduating after another 3 semesters here (Fall 2020). I know I want to take CS 189, and in preparation I plan on taking both EECS 127 and STAT 140.

Does anyone know what the workload for taking both STAT 140 + EECS 127 next fall would look like for me, and would taking both in the same semester lead well into taking CS 189 the spring after? I plan on taking no other techs next fall, and one other tech with 189 (either 61c or 182).

Otherwise, I was thinking of taking one of 140/127 next fall, the other one the spring after, and taking 189 my last semester here Fall 2020. Any suggestions as to which plan looks better?
history.subject: STAT 140 + EECS 127 Workload
